WEBVTT

1
00:00:05.680 --> 00:00:09.430
<i>Epic theme playing...</i>

2
00:00:11.000 --> 00:00:17.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

3
00:01:33.292 --> 00:01:36.661
<font color=#FF00FF>*HOUSE OF DRAGON*</font>
<font color=#00FF00>Season 01  Episode 03</font>

4
00:01:36.826 --> 00:01:39.441
Episode Title: <font color=#FFc30f>"Second of His Name"</font>
Aired on: <font color="#00ffff">September 04. 2022.</font>

5
00:02:19.662 --> 00:02:22.569
House Velaryon is coming for you!

6
00:02:22.992 --> 00:02:25.541
The Sea Snake will have
your poxy fucking head!

7
00:02:26.423 --> 00:02:28.819
No. no. no. No. please!

8
00:02:35.678 --> 00:02:38.155
Fuck you. Prince Drahar!

9
00:02:38.368 --> 00:02:41.871
Fuck your whore mother
and bastard father!

10
00:02:41.956 --> 00:02:43.858
Fuck!

11
00:02:44.381 --> 00:02:47.069
No. no! No!

12
00:03:11.213 --> 00:03:13.048
Dragon!

13
00:03:13.132 --> 00:03:15.491
Hail Prince Daemon!

14
00:03:17.998 --> 00:03:21.472
Burn the fucking
Triarchy cunts alive!

15
00:03:29.046 --> 00:03:30.436
Here. my Prince.

16
00:03:31.451 --> 00:03:32.887
Save me!

17
00:03:41.697 --> 00:03:43.873
To the caves! Now!

18
00:03:51.754 --> 00:03:53.772
Retreat to the caves!

19
00:04:16.108 --> 00:04:17.656
Where are you?

20
00:04:20.053 --> 00:04:22.983
Come out and face me. Drahar!

21
00:04:24.256 --> 00:04:26.295
Come out. Drahar!

22
00:04:26.763 --> 00:04:28.881
Where are you?

23
00:04:29.724 --> 00:04:32.287
I'm gonna feed you
to your own crabs!

24
00:04:33.170 --> 00:04:34.843
Where are you?

25
00:05:12.752 --> 00:05:14.211
He has your hair. Your Grace.

26
00:05:15.365 --> 00:05:16.649
He does have my hair.

27
00:05:16.733 --> 00:05:19.437
- He has your eyes. Your Grace.
- Yes. he does.

28
00:05:21.646 --> 00:05:22.936
And you have my nose.
don't you?

29
00:05:23.021 --> 00:05:27.077
Two years old and already
our boy has a kingly presence.

30
00:05:27.596 --> 00:05:28.851
He may yet. brother.

31
00:05:28.936 --> 00:05:30.653
but this morning
he insisted on eating

32
00:05:30.738 --> 00:05:32.202
porridge with his hands.

33
00:05:32.287 --> 00:05:33.639
He

34
00:05:34.095 --> 00:05:35.506
will grow.

35
00:05:36.702 --> 00:05:39.639
We're quite a party
assembled in his honor.

36
00:05:40.372 --> 00:05:41.975
And surely by the end
of this hunt.

37
00:05:42.060 --> 00:05:43.787
we shall have more to celebrate.

38
00:05:43.998 --> 00:05:45.741
And what is that. pray tell.

39
00:05:46.069 --> 00:05:48.255
It is Aegon's second name day.

40
00:05:48.339 --> 00:05:50.006
His infancy's behind him.

41
00:05:50.350 --> 00:05:53.051
It only remains for Viserys to
name him heir to the throne.

42
00:05:53.135 --> 00:05:55.095
I wouldn't be so sure.

43
00:05:55.179 --> 00:05:56.805
He's the King's firstborn son.

44
00:05:56.889 --> 00:06:00.105
I don't know that His Grace
sees it so clearly.

45
00:06:01.518 --> 00:06:04.484
Then it lies with you
to make him see it...

46
00:06:04.690 --> 00:06:06.775
Lord Hand.

47
00:06:06.891 --> 00:06:08.939
Your Grace...

48
00:06:10.021 --> 00:06:12.940
I bring urgent news
from the Step stones.

49
00:06:13.180 --> 00:06:15.390
The Crabfeeder has dug in
for siege on Bloodstone

50
00:06:15.491 --> 00:06:16.992
while his men sabotage our fleet
under the cover of dark.

51
00:06:17.076 --> 00:06:19.272
Not today. Tyland.

52
00:06:19.357 --> 00:06:22.318
The matter of the Step stones
is regrettably urgent.

53
00:06:22.403 --> 00:06:24.321
It's been three years.

54
00:06:24.406 --> 00:06:26.829
It can wait another three days.

55
00:06:30.704 --> 00:06:32.747
Come. eat.

56
00:06:33.050 --> 00:06:35.022
Fortify yourselves
for the journey.

57
00:06:35.977 --> 00:06:37.562
Please.

58
00:06:38.302 --> 00:06:39.719
Is the baggage train ready?

59
00:06:39.890 --> 00:06:42.017
It is presently massing
at the River Gate.

60
00:06:42.101 --> 00:06:44.709
Lord Jason expects us
in the Kings wood before midday.

61
00:06:44.794 --> 00:06:48.302
- Have you seen Rhaenyra?
- I have not. Your Grace.

62
00:06:50.275 --> 00:06:53.235
With the Triarchy now sheltering
in Bloodstone's caves.

63
00:06:53.445 --> 00:06:55.514
the threat of the dragons
is blunted.

64
00:06:55.897 --> 00:06:57.974
They don't have foot soldiers.

65
00:06:58.242 --> 00:06:59.910
But their sell swords have been

66
00:06:59.994 --> 00:07:01.411
withdrawing in droves.
Your Grace.

67
00:07:01.495 --> 00:07:04.608
Even the mercenaries can
see that it is a losing effort.

68
00:07:04.756 --> 00:07:06.291
Where's Rhaenyra?

69
00:07:06.530 --> 00:07:08.210
I cannot be sure
at present. Your Grace.

70
00:07:08.294 --> 00:07:11.819
The Velaryon forces have
suffered heavy attrition. Your Grace.

71
00:07:12.274 --> 00:07:15.467
The seeds of dissent are
sown amongst the rank and file.

72
00:07:15.688 --> 00:07:17.606
Daemon has driven the men hard.

73
00:07:17.776 --> 00:07:20.600
They have begun
to question his command.

74
00:07:21.256 --> 00:07:23.842
If the crown were
ever to intervene...

75
00:07:23.927 --> 00:07:25.220
- Tyland...
- ...now is the time.

76
00:07:25.305 --> 00:07:27.561
Daemon and The Sea Snake
started their war

77
00:07:27.646 --> 00:07:29.647
without His Grace's leave.

78
00:07:29.732 --> 00:07:32.531
Were he to intervene
now after so long.

79
00:07:32.616 --> 00:07:34.402
it would make
the crown appear weak.

80
00:07:34.486 --> 00:07:36.053
Can someone tell me

81
00:07:36.138 --> 00:07:38.807
where in the Seven Hells
Rhaenyra might be?

82
00:07:38.969 --> 00:07:44.467
♪ Under the dragon's eye ♪

83
00:07:45.166 --> 00:07:50.327
♪ Under the dragon's eye ♪

84
00:07:50.919 --> 00:07:52.132
Again.

85
00:07:53.382 --> 00:07:55.592
Perhaps the Princess might
like to hear something else?

86
00:07:55.677 --> 00:07:57.725
She would not.
Play it again.

87
00:08:03.587 --> 00:08:06.798
♪ She fled with her ships ♪

88
00:08:06.883 --> 00:08:09.553
♪ And her people ♪

89
00:08:09.638 --> 00:08:12.891
♪ Her heart broken for those ♪

90
00:08:13.110 --> 00:08:15.237
Your Grace.

91
00:08:15.321 --> 00:08:16.910
Did I say to stop?

92
00:08:21.596 --> 00:08:23.393
From the beginning.

93
00:08:28.999 --> 00:08:31.881
♪ She fled with her ships ♪

94
00:08:31.966 --> 00:08:35.344
- Rhaenyra?
- Yes. my Queen?

95
00:08:35.505 --> 00:08:37.798
Your presence is wanted
in the outer courtyard.

96
00:08:37.883 --> 00:08:40.218
The royal hunt
readies to depart.

97
00:08:40.363 --> 00:08:43.287
I've decided to remain here
and read instead.

98
00:08:45.098 --> 00:08:47.183
You may go. Sam well.

99
00:08:47.376 --> 00:08:49.787
You are to stay
by order of the Princess.

100
00:08:50.455 --> 00:08:53.537
The Queen commands you
to leave the Godswood at once.

101
00:08:55.916 --> 00:08:57.130
Princess.

102
00:09:00.344 --> 00:09:01.558
Your Grace.

103
00:09:05.088 --> 00:09:06.772
The King wishes
for you to join us.

104
00:09:06.912 --> 00:09:08.330
The King has
much to celebrate.

105
00:09:08.414 --> 00:09:09.706
He does not need me.

106
00:09:09.790 --> 00:09:11.671
He wants for us
all to be together.

107
00:09:12.339 --> 00:09:15.366
Perhaps the hunt
could be... fun.

108
00:09:16.422 --> 00:09:18.631
Is it the King's command?

109
00:09:19.311 --> 00:09:21.806
- Yes. but it...
- Then at once. Your Grace.

110
00:09:22.547 --> 00:09:24.507
But it needn't be.

111
00:09:24.763 --> 00:09:28.438
None of it needs be this way
in truth. Rhaenyra.

112
00:09:37.067 --> 00:09:38.905
Well. isn't this splendid.

113
00:09:39.225 --> 00:09:43.350
The whole of our family off to celebration
and adventure in the Kings wood.

114
00:09:49.965 --> 00:09:52.077
Should you be traveling
in such condition?

115
00:09:52.162 --> 00:09:55.540
The maester said that being
out in nature would do me well.

116
00:09:55.625 --> 00:09:58.561
Well. you will be with your
own child sooner than late.

117
00:09:58.890 --> 00:10:01.342
and make me a proud grand sire.

118
00:10:02.657 --> 00:10:04.577
It's not so bad.

119
00:10:04.662 --> 00:10:08.467
The days are long. but Aegon
came quickly and without fuss.

120
00:10:15.999 --> 00:10:18.381
You should ride out
with me today.

121
00:10:19.306 --> 00:10:20.873
Join in the chase.

122
00:10:21.019 --> 00:10:22.937
I'd rather not.

123
00:10:23.037 --> 00:10:26.206
The boars squeal like children
when they're being slaughtered.

124
00:10:26.291 --> 00:10:28.748
I find it discomforting.

125
00:10:28.833 --> 00:10:30.125
It's a hunt. Rhaenyra.

126
00:10:33.125 --> 00:10:35.498
How would you like
to participate?

127
00:10:35.743 --> 00:10:37.178
I'm not sure why I must.

128
00:10:37.263 --> 00:10:39.373
Because you are my daughter...

129
00:10:39.552 --> 00:10:41.233
The Princess.

130
00:10:41.318 --> 00:10:43.061
And you have duties.

131
00:10:43.172 --> 00:10:45.048
As I am ceaselessly reminded.

132
00:10:45.312 --> 00:10:48.023
- I'm sorry?
- As I am ceaselessly reminded.

133
00:10:48.108 --> 00:10:50.787
You wouldn't need to be reminded
if you ever attended to them.

134
00:10:51.153 --> 00:10:52.920
No one's here for me.

135
00:11:54.900 --> 00:11:58.668
Hail. hail Aegon. the
Conqueror-Babe. Second of His Name!

136
00:11:58.958 --> 00:12:02.262
Here's to His Grace
on his second name day!

137
00:12:48.575 --> 00:12:51.619
Lady Johanna
was reported to have been abducted

138
00:12:51.720 --> 00:12:54.668
when one of Lord Swann's ships
sailed through the Step stones.

139
00:12:54.753 --> 00:12:56.504
What will happen
to Lady Johanna?

140
00:12:56.589 --> 00:12:58.302
She's to be sold to a pillow house

141
00:12:58.387 --> 00:12:59.435
in the Free Cities

142
00:12:59.519 --> 00:13:01.818
if you believe the rumors.

143
00:13:02.895 --> 00:13:05.395
I fear the gods did not
make me for hunting.

144
00:13:05.480 --> 00:13:07.182
Might I sit with you.
my ladies?

145
00:13:07.267 --> 00:13:09.685
But of course. Please join us.

146
00:13:09.770 --> 00:13:13.315
Larys Strong. the youngest son
of our Master of Law. Lord Lyonel.

147
00:13:13.400 --> 00:13:14.866
My Lord husband
says that no King

148
00:13:14.951 --> 00:13:17.562
has even been able to tame
the Step stones for long.

149
00:13:17.646 --> 00:13:20.598
It's an inhospitable place
suited only for savages.

150
00:13:20.683 --> 00:13:24.842
Perhaps the Princess...
can give us some insight.

151
00:13:25.021 --> 00:13:27.530
Oh. I'm not sure how I could.

152
00:13:27.615 --> 00:13:28.975
I've never been
to the Step stones.

153
00:13:29.174 --> 00:13:32.301
Your dear uncle is the
great mind behind this war.

154
00:13:32.393 --> 00:13:34.136
- Is he not?
- I wouldn't know.

155
00:13:34.221 --> 00:13:35.638
I've not spoken
to Daemon in years.

156
00:13:35.722 --> 00:13:37.724
Since you supplanted
him as heir.

157
00:13:37.808 --> 00:13:40.309
Daemon made his choices.
Lady Ceira.

158
00:13:40.394 --> 00:13:43.021
The Princess was
more suited to the role.

159
00:13:43.315 --> 00:13:46.276
He's made a mess
and the King must put an end to it.

160
00:13:46.415 --> 00:13:47.774
Send fleets and men

161
00:13:47.859 --> 00:13:50.832
and clear out
the Triarchy for good.

162
00:13:51.675 --> 00:13:54.052
But the crown is not at war.

163
00:13:54.144 --> 00:13:57.230
The crown...
is at war. Princess.

164
00:13:57.315 --> 00:13:59.114
Though your father
refuses to admit it.

165
00:13:59.199 --> 00:14:02.026
we've been dragged into it by
your uncle and The Sea Snake.

166
00:14:02.113 --> 00:14:03.512
And how have you served
the realm of late.

167
00:14:03.596 --> 00:14:05.769
Lady Redwyne. by eating cake?

168
00:14:38.654 --> 00:14:40.655
I wonder. Princess...

169
00:14:40.779 --> 00:14:44.074
was your own second name day
as grand as this?

170
00:14:44.283 --> 00:14:47.186
I honestly don't recall
and neither will Aegon.

171
00:14:49.636 --> 00:14:51.396
Lord Jason Lannister.

172
00:14:52.290 --> 00:14:54.326
I gathered that
from all the lions.

173
00:14:54.560 --> 00:14:56.982
I don't think we've been
properly introduced.

174
00:14:59.107 --> 00:15:02.959
Your twin serves
on my father's council.

175
00:15:03.170 --> 00:15:05.279
Tyland is...

176
00:15:05.631 --> 00:15:08.857
frightfully dull.
gods love him.

177
00:15:09.065 --> 00:15:10.602
The finest honeyed wine
you'll ever taste.

178
00:15:10.686 --> 00:15:13.482
- Made in Lannisport. of course.
- Of course.

179
00:15:14.974 --> 00:15:18.060
Ah. the Kings wood.
it's fine hunting ground.

180
00:15:18.223 --> 00:15:20.850
But the best spot is to be
found at Casterly Rock.

181
00:15:20.935 --> 00:15:22.396
near my home.

182
00:15:22.628 --> 00:15:24.004
Have you been?

183
00:15:24.089 --> 00:15:26.456
Um. once... on tour

184
00:15:26.541 --> 00:15:28.046
with my mother when I was young.

185
00:15:28.131 --> 00:15:30.662
and honestly can't recall
much of that either.

186
00:15:30.747 --> 00:15:33.451
The Rock is thrice the height
of the High tower in Old town.

187
00:15:33.536 --> 00:15:35.370
taller still than
the Wall in the north.

188
00:15:35.575 --> 00:15:37.015
It's been said that

189
00:15:37.100 --> 00:15:40.506
if one were to stand in the
tower... on a perfect day.

190
00:15:40.591 --> 00:15:43.515
one could see clear
across the Sunset Sea.

191
00:15:44.027 --> 00:15:45.576
It must be quite something.

192
00:15:45.711 --> 00:15:48.201
Hm. I don't have a Dragon pit.
of course. but...

193
00:15:48.967 --> 00:15:51.891
I do have the means
and resources to build one.

194
00:15:52.505 --> 00:15:54.850
Why would you need a Dragon pit?

195
00:15:55.364 --> 00:15:57.365
To house dragons. of course.

196
00:15:57.450 --> 00:15:59.373
I'd do anything for my Queen...

197
00:16:00.303 --> 00:16:02.771
or... lady wife.

198
00:16:08.862 --> 00:16:11.052
Thank you for the wine.

199
00:16:24.439 --> 00:16:26.100
Is that what I am to you?

200
00:16:26.652 --> 00:16:29.779
A prize to proffer about
to the great houses?

201
00:16:34.057 --> 00:16:36.201
You're of age. Rhaenyra.

202
00:16:37.186 --> 00:16:39.140
And Jason Lannister
is an excellent match.

203
00:16:39.225 --> 00:16:40.835
He's arrogant
and self-serious.

204
00:16:40.920 --> 00:16:42.913
Well. I thought you might
have that in common.

205
00:16:44.121 --> 00:16:45.740
Since you came of age.

206
00:16:45.844 --> 00:16:48.079
I've been slowly drowning
in a lake of parchment

207
00:16:48.164 --> 00:16:49.904
flung from every
corner of the realm.

208
00:16:49.989 --> 00:16:51.782
Marriage proposals. all.

209
00:16:51.896 --> 00:16:53.585
And I have tried often

210
00:16:53.670 --> 00:16:55.087
to discuss it with you.

211
00:16:55.171 --> 00:16:56.748
but you've refused me
at every turn.

212
00:16:56.833 --> 00:16:58.693
That is because I do not
wish to get married.

213
00:16:58.778 --> 00:17:00.515
Even I do
not exist above tradition

214
00:17:00.600 --> 00:17:01.507
and duty. Rhaenyra!

215
00:17:01.592 --> 00:17:04.120
- Excuse...
- Excuse me. Your Grace.

216
00:17:11.422 --> 00:17:13.146
You must marry.

217
00:17:15.935 --> 00:17:16.947
Yes?

218
00:17:17.031 --> 00:17:19.091
The royal huntsman have
sent a report. Your Grace.

219
00:17:19.176 --> 00:17:22.191
There's been a sighting
of a white hart.

220
00:17:23.700 --> 00:17:26.061
The stag is "The King of
the Kings wood." Your Grace.

221
00:17:26.146 --> 00:17:28.913
A regal portent for
Prince Aegon's name day.

222
00:17:51.076 --> 00:17:52.707
Princess.

223
00:17:58.698 --> 00:18:00.560
Princess. wait!

224
00:18:20.199 --> 00:18:21.904
Princess. slow down!

225
00:18:28.595 --> 00:18:31.055
Hyah. hyah. hyah!

226
00:18:31.140 --> 00:18:34.810
Princess!

227
00:18:35.018 --> 00:18:36.951
No!

228
00:18:37.232 --> 00:18:40.823
Whoa. whoa. now!

229
00:18:48.670 --> 00:18:50.873
What happened back there?

230
00:18:51.486 --> 00:18:53.208
My father...

231
00:18:53.865 --> 00:18:57.029
trying to sell me off
to Jason Lannister.

232
00:18:59.105 --> 00:19:02.756
Was... was I named heir
to the Iron Throne

233
00:19:02.841 --> 00:19:05.318
so that I might only
further raise the standing

234
00:19:05.529 --> 00:19:07.795
of a Lord of Casterly Rock?

235
00:19:10.974 --> 00:19:12.865
Do you want me to kill him?

236
00:19:18.314 --> 00:19:21.295
We should return to camp. Princess.

237
00:19:24.450 --> 00:19:26.170
It's a beautiful day.

238
00:19:26.918 --> 00:19:28.888
We should take in the Kings wood.

239
00:19:34.572 --> 00:19:37.157
Were you ever betrothed.
Ser Criston?

240
00:19:37.374 --> 00:19:40.052
I had an adventurous
youth when my father

241
00:19:40.137 --> 00:19:42.238
served at Blackhaven.
to be sure.

242
00:19:42.607 --> 00:19:44.560
But my station was
never high enough

243
00:19:44.645 --> 00:19:46.215
for a formal betrothal.

244
00:19:46.448 --> 00:19:48.435
Before I spoke my vows as
a knight of the Kings guard.

245
00:19:48.519 --> 00:19:50.571
I could've married
a common-born girl had I wished.

246
00:19:50.679 --> 00:19:53.887
How lucky you are to have
a say in your own life.

247
00:19:54.100 --> 00:19:57.358
Many in the realm would gladly
trade positions with you. Princess.

248
00:19:58.972 --> 00:20:02.481
Only because none of them
has ever held my position.

249
00:20:03.068 --> 00:20:04.989
I may be the Princess
of Dragons tone.

250
00:20:05.074 --> 00:20:06.457
but I am toothless.

251
00:20:08.607 --> 00:20:10.071
One day...

252
00:20:10.877 --> 00:20:12.410
not so long ago.

253
00:20:12.832 --> 00:20:14.849
you held enough power
to write my name

254
00:20:14.934 --> 00:20:16.684
into the White Book.

255
00:20:16.956 --> 00:20:18.589
And when your father
named me to his Kings guard.

256
00:20:18.673 --> 00:20:20.804
it was the highest honor
any Cole have ever known.

257
00:20:22.213 --> 00:20:23.723
All that I have. I owe to you.

258
00:20:26.194 --> 00:20:29.327
Now I'd hardly call that
toothless. Princess.

259
00:21:01.558 --> 00:21:03.749
- Your Grace.
- How far?

260
00:21:03.834 --> 00:21:06.402
Her droppings were found
half a league to the east.

261
00:21:09.347 --> 00:21:11.927
Still fresh.

262
00:21:12.035 --> 00:21:14.121
Between two and
three hours. Your Grace.

263
00:21:14.206 --> 00:21:15.999
My best scouts spied him.

264
00:21:16.224 --> 00:21:18.559
The beast is upward of 35 stone.

265
00:21:18.643 --> 00:21:20.708
And we now have his trail.

266
00:21:20.793 --> 00:21:24.004
- Aye.
- Before the dragons ruled over Westeros.

267
00:21:24.089 --> 00:21:27.005
the white hart was a symbol
of royalty in these lands.

268
00:21:28.344 --> 00:21:30.755
And on this day of all days.

269
00:21:31.227 --> 00:21:34.154
I've never been one for signs
and portents. Your Grace.

270
00:21:34.239 --> 00:21:37.231
but if the gods did wish
to show their favor.

271
00:21:58.353 --> 00:22:00.122
Oh!

272
00:22:19.325 --> 00:22:21.364
Your Grace...

273
00:22:23.929 --> 00:22:27.966
I had this forged in the Golden
Gallery in honor of Prince Aegon.

274
00:22:39.544 --> 00:22:41.489
It's quite a thing.

275
00:22:42.432 --> 00:22:45.898
I hope it might provide the killing
stroke against your white hart.

276
00:22:48.552 --> 00:22:50.600
The King of the Kings wood.

277
00:22:52.278 --> 00:22:55.161
It's as if the Seven themselves
have blessed this day.

278
00:22:55.289 --> 00:22:58.379
Thank you...
for your generosity.

279
00:23:01.169 --> 00:23:03.341
I would be honored

280
00:23:03.944 --> 00:23:07.129
to take the Princess Rhaenyra
to wife. Your Grace.

281
00:23:08.330 --> 00:23:09.950
What I offer you.

282
00:23:10.099 --> 00:23:12.083
The crown and your daughter.

283
00:23:12.337 --> 00:23:14.067
is strength.

284
00:23:15.981 --> 00:23:20.122
Do you think that House
Targaryen wants for strength?

285
00:23:20.549 --> 00:23:22.133
If someone offered
you more dragons.

286
00:23:22.286 --> 00:23:24.005
would you not take them?

287
00:23:24.276 --> 00:23:26.755
Do you have dragons to offer?

288
00:23:29.385 --> 00:23:31.458
Casterly Rock
is a splendid seat.

289
00:23:31.814 --> 00:23:34.911
Rhaenyra may take her place
there by my side without shame.

290
00:23:35.106 --> 00:23:36.822
and feel herself
well-compensated

291
00:23:36.906 --> 00:23:38.427
for her loss in station.

292
00:23:38.708 --> 00:23:40.810
What loss of station?

293
00:23:41.744 --> 00:23:44.880
If you were to name
young Aegon heir. Your Grace.

294
00:23:45.152 --> 00:23:47.450
And when would I be doing that?

295
00:23:48.492 --> 00:23:52.153
I had assumed...
as he's your firstborn son...

296
00:23:52.372 --> 00:23:55.247
- Many of us had assumed...
- Many of us. you say?

297
00:23:56.341 --> 00:23:58.903
Have your bannermen
questioned my choice of heir?

298
00:23:59.024 --> 00:24:00.287
Of course not. Your Grace.

299
00:24:00.372 --> 00:24:02.598
It is your sworn duty
to report rebellion

300
00:24:02.682 --> 00:24:04.850
- stirring in my kingdom.
- Rebellion?

301
00:24:04.934 --> 00:24:07.638
There's been nothing of
the sort. Your Grace. I. I...

302
00:24:07.723 --> 00:24:11.517
I did not decide to name
Rhaenyra my heir on a whim.

303
00:24:12.723 --> 00:24:16.339
All the lords of the kingdom
would do well to remember that.

304
00:24:19.237 --> 00:24:22.144
Thank you... for the gift.

305
00:24:25.383 --> 00:24:26.761
Your Grace.

306
00:24:31.252 --> 00:24:32.670
Wine.

307
00:24:45.333 --> 00:24:47.434
The huntsman
has the trail. Your Grace.

308
00:24:47.518 --> 00:24:49.061
and has sent out
the hounds.

309
00:24:49.145 --> 00:24:51.934
It won't be long now until
the white hart is cornered.

310
00:24:52.019 --> 00:24:54.199
Your prize is within reach.

311
00:24:56.078 --> 00:24:59.540
What do you make of
Lord Jason's proposal?

312
00:24:59.640 --> 00:25:02.480
That man's pride has pride.

313
00:25:05.636 --> 00:25:08.527
You're not only Rhaenyra's
father. you're the King.

314
00:25:10.001 --> 00:25:11.590
She'll do as you command.

315
00:25:13.000 --> 00:25:15.355
It is not my wish
to command her. Otto.

316
00:25:16.413 --> 00:25:18.712
I want her to be happy.

317
00:25:24.363 --> 00:25:27.496
There is another choice
beyond Casterly Rock.

318
00:25:28.440 --> 00:25:31.919
One. perhaps. you might
be more comfortable with.

319
00:25:32.004 --> 00:25:35.174
One... closer to home.

320
00:25:35.401 --> 00:25:36.902
Who do you have in mind?

321
00:25:40.664 --> 00:25:42.286
Prince Aegon.

322
00:25:51.005 --> 00:25:52.840
The boy just turned two. Otto.

323
00:25:53.120 --> 00:25:56.873
Yes. but it would cease the endless
proposals for Rhaenyra's hand.

324
00:25:59.580 --> 00:26:02.575
- Betroth them.
- I came here to hunt...

325
00:26:02.968 --> 00:26:07.143
not to be suffocated by
all this fucking politicking.

326
00:26:08.210 --> 00:26:09.708
Let us speak no more of it.

327
00:27:02.689 --> 00:27:06.317
We've sent out
riders to find Rhaenyra. Your Grace.

328
00:27:06.722 --> 00:27:07.889
Ser Criston went after her.

329
00:27:07.974 --> 00:27:09.475
so the hope is that
they are together.

330
00:27:09.560 --> 00:27:12.075
The girl is
a heedless contrarian.

331
00:27:13.174 --> 00:27:15.676
If I instead forbade her
to wed a Lannister.

332
00:27:15.994 --> 00:27:19.418
she would've run off
with Lord Jason out of spite.

333
00:27:20.778 --> 00:27:23.849
A truly great
Targaryen King I am.

334
00:27:24.211 --> 00:27:27.606
Powerless over mine own
daughter of seven-and-ten.

335
00:27:28.544 --> 00:27:31.130
King Jaehaerys ruled over
half a century of peace

336
00:27:31.214 --> 00:27:34.419
while his children drove him
to the edge of madness...

337
00:27:34.504 --> 00:27:36.756
his daughters. in particular.

338
00:27:37.047 --> 00:27:39.507
It is tradition. Your Grace.

339
00:27:46.239 --> 00:27:48.954
Do you wish to hear
my opinion on the matter?

340
00:27:53.241 --> 00:27:55.289
Should I guess?

341
00:27:57.169 --> 00:27:58.975
You believe that your son.

342
00:27:59.060 --> 00:28:01.410
Ser Harwin "Break bones."

343
00:28:01.494 --> 00:28:04.830
the strongest knight
in the Seven Kingdoms.

344
00:28:04.914 --> 00:28:07.463
is the best match for Rhaenyra.

345
00:28:08.834 --> 00:28:11.122
You flatter me.
Your Grace. but no.

346
00:28:11.974 --> 00:28:15.966
It would seem to me the best match for
Rhaenyra is the son of The Sea Snake.

347
00:28:16.050 --> 00:28:17.724
Ser Laenor.

348
00:28:18.347 --> 00:28:21.433
Some years ago. I counseled
you to take his sister to wife.

349
00:28:21.634 --> 00:28:23.950
My reasoning remains the same.

350
00:28:24.545 --> 00:28:27.849
Laenor is of pure
Valyrian descent.

351
00:28:28.104 --> 00:28:31.325
He shares blood with your
cousin. the Princess Rhaenys.

352
00:28:31.608 --> 00:28:35.032
And he is the heir to the
wealthiest house in the realm.

353
00:28:36.075 --> 00:28:37.607
The breach between your houses

354
00:28:37.692 --> 00:28:39.198
has not narrowed since
I last spoke of it.

355
00:28:39.282 --> 00:28:41.616
It would do much
to assuage Lord Corlys

356
00:28:41.701 --> 00:28:44.794
of any slights real...
or imagined.

357
00:28:50.222 --> 00:28:52.629
We must pray. of course.
that Laenor survives

358
00:28:52.714 --> 00:28:54.555
the fighting in the Step stones.

359
00:29:33.044 --> 00:29:36.260
Princess. I must make a final
plea that we return to the camp.

360
00:29:37.507 --> 00:29:39.216
I rather prefer it here.

361
00:29:41.469 --> 00:29:44.161
His Grace is certain to be
worried by your absence.

362
00:29:44.692 --> 00:29:48.873
His Grace can worry
himself to death if he so likes.

363
00:29:58.979 --> 00:30:01.364
Tell me something. Ser Criston.

364
00:30:02.359 --> 00:30:05.419
Do you think the realm will
ever accept me as their Queen?

365
00:30:12.921 --> 00:30:15.255
They'll have no choice
but to. Princess.

366
00:32:11.619 --> 00:32:13.411
Is everything all right.
Your Grace?

367
00:32:17.470 --> 00:32:18.971
You know. I...

368
00:32:19.583 --> 00:32:24.136
I named her... to protect
the realm from Daemon.

369
00:32:26.676 --> 00:32:28.432
She was my only child.

370
00:32:30.096 --> 00:32:31.942
"The Realm's Delight."

371
00:32:32.903 --> 00:32:34.864
I named her out of love

372
00:32:36.102 --> 00:32:38.525
because I no longer believed...

373
00:32:39.646 --> 00:32:41.611
Believed what. my love?

374
00:32:49.699 --> 00:32:52.981
Many in my line have
been dragon riders.

375
00:32:54.823 --> 00:32:57.539
Very few among us
have been dreamers.

376
00:33:01.752 --> 00:33:03.997
What is the power of a dragon...

377
00:33:04.505 --> 00:33:06.256
next to the power of prophecy.

378
00:33:06.341 --> 00:33:07.990
The hour is too late. husband.

379
00:33:08.075 --> 00:33:10.140
When Rhaenyra was a child...

380
00:33:10.965 --> 00:33:12.896
I saw it in a dream...

381
00:33:14.210 --> 00:33:16.800
as vivid as these flames.
I saw it.

382
00:33:18.278 --> 00:33:21.099
A male babe born to me...

383
00:33:21.973 --> 00:33:24.231
wearing the Conqueror's crown.

384
00:33:26.386 --> 00:33:28.325
And I so wanted it to be true.

385
00:33:29.155 --> 00:33:30.841
to be a dreamer myself.

386
00:33:33.281 --> 00:33:36.414
I sought that vision again.
night after night...

387
00:33:37.809 --> 00:33:39.341
but it never came again.

388
00:33:41.297 --> 00:33:44.349
I poured all my thought
and will into it.

389
00:33:47.173 --> 00:33:49.834
And my obsession killed
Rhaenyra's mother.

390
00:33:49.919 --> 00:33:51.856
Viserys.

391
00:33:52.261 --> 00:33:57.317
I thought Rhaenyra was the way
out of my abyss of grief and regret.

392
00:33:59.060 --> 00:34:01.726
And naming her heir would
begin to set things right.

393
00:34:01.811 --> 00:34:04.985
- Oh. it did.
- I never imagined I would remarry...

394
00:34:05.483 --> 00:34:07.350
that I would have a son.

395
00:34:12.179 --> 00:34:14.192
What if I was wrong?

396
00:35:16.013 --> 00:35:17.552
Left.

397
00:35:25.474 --> 00:35:27.677
He may not be white. Your Grace.

398
00:35:27.898 --> 00:35:29.107
But he's a big lad.

399
00:35:36.115 --> 00:35:38.888
Your Grace... for the kill.

400
00:36:04.792 --> 00:36:07.331
Right here. Your Grace.

401
00:36:36.990 --> 00:36:38.755
One more time. Your Grace.

402
00:36:38.840 --> 00:36:40.594
A little bit to your left.

403
00:38:11.462 --> 00:38:13.308
No.

404
00:39:35.904 --> 00:39:37.497
Come. sweet Prince.

405
00:39:37.623 --> 00:39:39.169
Let's give Her Grace
some peace.

406
00:39:54.373 --> 00:39:56.388
Did you enjoy the hunt.
Your Grace?

407
00:39:57.376 --> 00:40:01.232
- Well enough.
- How fared my grandson?

408
00:40:02.006 --> 00:40:04.638
The ladies Lannister and
Redwyne were quite taken with him.

409
00:40:04.723 --> 00:40:06.349
As they should be.

410
00:40:07.558 --> 00:40:09.606
He's the future of the realm.

411
00:40:11.155 --> 00:40:14.311
Well. you yourself witnessed
the scale of the celebration.

412
00:40:14.396 --> 00:40:16.458
how it's united the men.

413
00:40:16.770 --> 00:40:18.225
When you bore the King a son.

414
00:40:18.310 --> 00:40:21.487
you ended 15 years
of uncertainty and doubt.

415
00:40:22.309 --> 00:40:23.810
Aegon. like his namesake.

416
00:40:23.919 --> 00:40:26.701
was born to rule
the Seven Kingdoms.

417
00:40:26.892 --> 00:40:28.602
If Viserys were
to name him heir.

418
00:40:28.717 --> 00:40:31.015
the realm would
fete him for it.

419
00:40:36.832 --> 00:40:38.787
And does this not please you?

420
00:40:38.872 --> 00:40:42.865
- Do you not want your son to be King?
- And what mother wouldn't?

421
00:40:43.581 --> 00:40:45.577
You mustn't ignore
the certain truth

422
00:40:45.662 --> 00:40:48.843
that if Rhaenyra were to step
over Aegon to ascend the throne.

423
00:40:48.934 --> 00:40:51.274
the realm would
tear itself apart.

424
00:40:53.182 --> 00:40:56.393
They all swore obeisance to her.
our house among them.

425
00:40:56.516 --> 00:40:58.522
That was before Aegon.

426
00:40:59.855 --> 00:41:01.466
Rhaenyra will be a good queen.

427
00:41:01.701 --> 00:41:05.544
It wouldn't matter if she were
Jaehaerys himself born again.

428
00:41:07.654 --> 00:41:10.573
- Rhaenyra is a woman.
- What of my son?

429
00:41:10.657 --> 00:41:13.618
Would you have me raise a man
to steal his own sister's birthright?

430
00:41:13.702 --> 00:41:16.466
It is Aegon that's being robbed.

431
00:41:16.705 --> 00:41:18.665
He's the firstborn
son of the King.

432
00:41:18.749 --> 00:41:20.875
To deny that he
is heir to the throne

433
00:41:20.960 --> 00:41:23.646
is to assail the laws
of gods and men.

434
00:41:25.310 --> 00:41:29.326
The road ahead is uncertain.
but the end is clear.

435
00:41:29.441 --> 00:41:31.447
Aegon will be king.

436
00:41:33.180 --> 00:41:36.083
You must guide
Viserys towards reason.

437
00:41:38.727 --> 00:41:40.775
<i>He'll never find it on his own.</i>

438
00:41:48.654 --> 00:41:50.139
How are you feeling. husband?

439
00:41:50.224 --> 00:41:53.131
The gods have punished me
for my indulgences.

440
00:41:54.146 --> 00:41:55.590
At least the wine was good.

441
00:41:55.675 --> 00:41:57.263
Too good.

442
00:42:09.227 --> 00:42:11.310
I was hoping we might
discuss something.

443
00:42:14.427 --> 00:42:15.807
Rhaenyra?

444
00:42:19.810 --> 00:42:22.623
I do not think she enjoyed
Jason Lannister's company.

445
00:42:23.564 --> 00:42:25.318
She is cross.

446
00:42:25.748 --> 00:42:27.582
I warned you that she would be.

447
00:42:27.776 --> 00:42:29.736
Rhaenyra has come of age.

448
00:42:29.820 --> 00:42:31.616
She must needs
marry a high lord

449
00:42:31.701 --> 00:42:32.843
who will honor her.
defend her.

450
00:42:32.927 --> 00:42:34.748
and serve her as king consort.

451
00:42:35.150 --> 00:42:37.860
Her wishes in this matter
are irrelevant.

452
00:42:38.078 --> 00:42:41.162
I do believe that Rhaenyra
will marry. Your Grace.

453
00:42:41.841 --> 00:42:44.270
But she must believe
it is her choice to do so.

454
00:42:53.502 --> 00:42:55.982
- What's this?
- A letter...

455
00:42:57.958 --> 00:43:00.044
from Vaemond Velaryon.

456
00:43:00.254 --> 00:43:03.169
- The Sea Snake's brother.
- Yeah.

457
00:43:03.807 --> 00:43:06.100
He's fighting
in the Step stones.

458
00:43:06.356 --> 00:43:08.099
with all the rest of them.

459
00:43:13.422 --> 00:43:15.068
May I?

460
00:43:25.393 --> 00:43:28.076
Lord Corlys and Prince Daemon
are losing their war.

461
00:43:28.701 --> 00:43:30.958
Badly. by all accounts.

462
00:43:31.686 --> 00:43:33.692
This is a plea for aid.

463
00:43:36.177 --> 00:43:37.990
Then why not send it?

464
00:43:38.075 --> 00:43:41.240
Because it is a war
started by two malcontents.

465
00:43:41.391 --> 00:43:43.689
unhappy with decisions I made.

466
00:43:44.960 --> 00:43:47.685
If I now provide
Daemon and Corlys succor.

467
00:43:48.138 --> 00:43:49.633
what will that say
of their king?

468
00:43:49.733 --> 00:43:52.569
Perhaps. that he is a good
man who loves his brother.

469
00:43:52.654 --> 00:43:55.255
Well. if you truly
believe that. my dear...

470
00:43:56.031 --> 00:43:58.388
then you possess
a generous spirit.

471
00:43:59.704 --> 00:44:01.912
What do you believe. Viserys?

472
00:44:05.286 --> 00:44:07.694
That I am forever doomed
to anger one person

473
00:44:07.779 --> 00:44:09.599
in the pleasing of another.

474
00:44:10.045 --> 00:44:12.310
Then I pose a simpler question.

475
00:44:13.048 --> 00:44:15.873
Is it better for the realm
if the Crabfeeder thrives.

476
00:44:16.093 --> 00:44:17.537
or is vanquished?

477
00:44:24.458 --> 00:44:26.477
Make haste
to Dwarfstone. Ser Addam.

478
00:44:26.561 --> 00:44:28.841
Hand-deliver this
to Prince Daemon yourself.

479
00:44:29.052 --> 00:44:30.736
At once. Your Grace.

480
00:44:39.115 --> 00:44:42.409
- Dwarfstone?
- I'm sending word to Daemon.

481
00:44:42.619 --> 00:44:44.841
Aid is sailing
to the Step stones.

482
00:44:46.123 --> 00:44:49.263
- Did he make call for help?
- He would sooner die.

483
00:44:50.002 --> 00:44:52.349
But his king does not
mean to allow that.

484
00:44:56.842 --> 00:44:59.021
Do you not think
my decision correct?

485
00:44:59.219 --> 00:45:01.513
It is no consequence
to what I think...

486
00:45:01.763 --> 00:45:03.728
as I'm often reminded.

487
00:45:06.114 --> 00:45:08.628
Daemon is thorn enough
in my flesh.

488
00:45:09.325 --> 00:45:11.917
Will you insist
on taking after him?

489
00:45:12.816 --> 00:45:14.621
Must everything be a battle?

490
00:45:14.706 --> 00:45:18.143
If you refer to your attempt to
marry me off to Casterly Rock.

491
00:45:18.245 --> 00:45:20.862
I am sorry. Rhaenyra.

492
00:45:22.064 --> 00:45:23.948
I was trying to help you.

493
00:45:24.453 --> 00:45:26.026
Will you not be helped?

494
00:45:26.788 --> 00:45:30.151
Why must every effort
on your behalf be resisted

495
00:45:30.334 --> 00:45:33.471
- as if to the death?
- Because you mean to replace me...

496
00:45:34.152 --> 00:45:36.279
with Alicent Hightower's son.

497
00:45:36.682 --> 00:45:39.042
the boy you always wanted.

498
00:45:39.551 --> 00:45:40.871
You have him in hands now.

499
00:45:40.956 --> 00:45:43.729
Y-You have no
further use for me.

500
00:45:43.972 --> 00:45:46.214
You might as well peddle me
for what you can.

501
00:45:46.475 --> 00:45:49.714
A mountain stronghold
or a fleet of ships.

502
00:45:49.991 --> 00:45:52.020
You have misjudged me. Rhaenyra.

503
00:45:52.105 --> 00:45:53.612
All know it.

504
00:45:54.066 --> 00:45:55.698
Jason Lannister knows it.

505
00:45:56.221 --> 00:45:57.735
You said it yourself.

506
00:45:57.819 --> 00:46:00.676
the lords of the realm gather
like vultures to a carcass.

507
00:46:00.761 --> 00:46:02.787
hoping to feast on my bones.

508
00:46:05.110 --> 00:46:09.030
It is true that as rulers
we must marry for advantage

509
00:46:09.443 --> 00:46:12.354
to forge alliances
and bolster our strength.

510
00:46:12.542 --> 00:46:15.112
You have always understood this.

511
00:46:15.670 --> 00:46:17.761
I myself was promised
to your mother when I was...

512
00:46:17.846 --> 00:46:20.215
Ten-and-seven years of age.

513
00:46:20.300 --> 00:46:22.240
The Vale had an army
to rival the North.

514
00:46:22.325 --> 00:46:24.550
I've heard that story
since I've had ears to.

515
00:46:25.865 --> 00:46:27.503
I loved her.

516
00:46:28.517 --> 00:46:30.147
She made a man of me.

517
00:46:33.563 --> 00:46:36.070
I do not seek
to replace you. child.

518
00:46:37.526 --> 00:46:39.800
You've been much alone
these last few years.

519
00:46:39.986 --> 00:46:41.909
Alone and angry.

520
00:46:43.323 --> 00:46:45.026
I will not live forever.

521
00:46:45.242 --> 00:46:47.118
I wish to see you contented.

522
00:46:47.202 --> 00:46:48.675
happy even.

523
00:46:48.870 --> 00:46:50.246
You think a man will do it?

524
00:46:50.331 --> 00:46:52.324
- A family.
- I had a family.

525
00:46:52.409 --> 00:46:53.847
What would you have me do?!

526
00:46:53.932 --> 00:46:57.104
If it was for advantage.
you would've wed Laena Velaryon!

527
00:47:01.804 --> 00:47:03.602
That is true enough.

528
00:47:06.190 --> 00:47:08.159
You must marry.

529
00:47:09.057 --> 00:47:11.042
strengthen your own claim.

530
00:47:11.685 --> 00:47:13.651
shore up your succession.

531
00:47:13.979 --> 00:47:15.610
multiply.

532
00:47:16.833 --> 00:47:18.503
As to your match...

533
00:47:20.197 --> 00:47:21.744
make it yourself.

534
00:47:22.737 --> 00:47:24.214
Search him out.

535
00:47:24.573 --> 00:47:26.339
Find one that pleases you.

536
00:47:26.749 --> 00:47:28.213
as I did.

537
00:47:43.717 --> 00:47:44.930
Rhaenyra...

538
00:47:50.783 --> 00:47:52.326
I did waver

539
00:47:52.737 --> 00:47:54.175
at one time.

540
00:47:55.395 --> 00:47:58.854
But I swear to you now.
on your mother's memory.

541
00:47:59.858 --> 00:48:01.737
you will not be supplanted.

542
00:48:45.403 --> 00:48:48.301
<i>We have 16.
perhaps 18. seaworthy ships.</i>

543
00:48:48.630 --> 00:48:51.036
<i>Seven hundred foot.
some 60 knights.</i>

544
00:48:51.121 --> 00:48:54.749
<i>Our food quickly dwindles. save
for what we can fish from the sea.</i>

545
00:48:54.871 --> 00:48:56.289
<i>I would say
we have a fortnight.</i>

546
00:48:56.458 --> 00:48:58.528
<i>mayhaps a bit longer
with strict rationing.</i>

547
00:48:59.042 --> 00:49:01.210
<i>I've made call for Driftmark
to send more ships.</i>

548
00:49:01.294 --> 00:49:03.364
<i>but they will be weeks away.</i>

549
00:49:03.622 --> 00:49:06.348
<i>We are faltering
and the Triarchy knows it.</i>

550
00:49:06.433 --> 00:49:09.894
<i>We must press the attack.
continue sending the dragons.</i>

551
00:49:10.267 --> 00:49:12.153
It's pointless. father.

552
00:49:12.590 --> 00:49:15.193
The Crabfeeder has
created a choke point here.

553
00:49:15.278 --> 00:49:16.833
beyond these dunes.

554
00:49:17.536 --> 00:49:18.978
Archers hold the high positions.

555
00:49:19.062 --> 00:49:20.771
foot soldiers hold the ground.

556
00:49:20.855 --> 00:49:22.935
We've strafed them on
dragon back again and again.

557
00:49:23.020 --> 00:49:25.067
but they just retreat
within the caves.

558
00:49:25.449 --> 00:49:28.895
Dragons can circle Bloodstone
until they fall out of the sky.

559
00:49:29.465 --> 00:49:30.448
The Crabfeeder and his men

560
00:49:30.532 --> 00:49:32.184
have no reason
to leave those caves.

561
00:49:32.269 --> 00:49:34.145
We must give them one.

562
00:49:34.326 --> 00:49:36.559
an offering of flesh
to bait the crab.

563
00:49:37.253 --> 00:49:38.587
Who?

564
00:49:38.786 --> 00:49:40.528
Dragon returning!

565
00:49:47.966 --> 00:49:49.473
Yes. Who?

566
00:49:49.558 --> 00:49:51.851
Which man here will
happily go to his death?

567
00:49:52.028 --> 00:49:54.318
Show me the knight
who will march into that hell pit.

568
00:49:54.403 --> 00:49:55.982
nephew. and I will
show you a madman.

569
00:49:56.067 --> 00:49:58.865
- Daemon.
- Daemon is why we are losing!

570
00:49:58.950 --> 00:50:01.270
He at least
is fighting this war.

571
00:50:01.354 --> 00:50:03.802
What role have you played
in his council. uncle.

572
00:50:03.887 --> 00:50:06.537
- other than Master of Complaints?
- Enough. Laenor.

573
00:50:06.622 --> 00:50:08.819
If King's Landing
will not support Daemon.

574
00:50:09.028 --> 00:50:10.738
why should any of us?!

575
00:50:16.872 --> 00:50:18.801
Blood or no. Vaemond.

576
00:50:19.164 --> 00:50:21.669
I will not have
you stoke mutiny.

577
00:50:42.479 --> 00:50:45.018
If you do not seize control
of this war. my lord.

578
00:50:45.103 --> 00:50:47.692
the crabs will soon
dine on all of us.

579
00:51:03.833 --> 00:51:05.075
Prince Daemon.

580
00:51:05.336 --> 00:51:08.005
I bring word from His Grace.
Viserys Targaryen.

581
00:51:08.129 --> 00:51:10.045
first of his name.
King of the Andals.

582
00:51:10.130 --> 00:51:11.840
the Rhoynar. and the First Men.

583
00:51:11.925 --> 00:51:14.481
Lord of the Seven Kingdoms.
and Protector of the Realm.

584
00:51:57.758 --> 00:52:01.805
That's enough! Stop!

585
00:52:16.539 --> 00:52:18.240
<i>Brother...</i>

586
00:52:18.352 --> 00:52:20.076
<i>I have ordered 10 ships</i>

587
00:52:20.160 --> 00:52:23.180
<i>and 2.000 men to set sail
from King's Landing</i>

588
00:52:23.265 --> 00:52:25.647
<i>to join the effort
in the Step stones.</i>

589
00:52:26.919 --> 00:52:30.219
<i>Though time and circumstance
have seen us estranged.</i>

590
00:52:30.501 --> 00:52:34.664
<i>know that it is not my desire
to see you fail in your cause.</i>

591
00:52:35.066 --> 00:52:37.726
<i>It is instead my hope
that this aid will deliver</i>

592
00:52:37.820 --> 00:52:40.742
<i>the victory that has
thus far evaded us.</i>

593
00:52:42.807 --> 00:52:46.357
<i>I shall pray nightly to
the gods for your safe return.</i>

594
00:54:40.049 --> 00:54:42.681
Nock.

595
00:55:05.856 --> 00:55:07.722
Draw.

596
00:55:47.069 --> 00:55:48.569
Loose!

597
00:55:56.111 --> 00:55:57.659
Loose!

598
00:56:13.267 --> 00:56:15.579
Loose!

599
00:56:32.995 --> 00:56:34.675
Loose!

600
00:59:15.644 --> 00:59:20.857
<i>Speaking High Valyrian...
Dracarys!</i>

601
00:59:30.901 --> 00:59:32.534
Nock!

602
00:59:33.342 --> 00:59:35.475
Dragon!

603
01:00:36.239 --> 01:00:38.078
Whoo!

604
01:00:54.580 --> 01:00:56.885
<i>Dracarys!</i>

605
01:00:57.305 --> 01:01:57.258
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today
